## **6. API Endpoints (Optional, but useful for APIs)**
List your main routes and their functions.

```markdown
## API Endpoints

('/users' RegisterUsers) -> User registration
('/verify-email' verifyEmail) -> Email verification after registration
('/users'  allUsers) -> To get the list of all users
('/users/:id' deleteUser) -> Delete a single user by id
('/users/:id'  updateUser) -> Update a single user by id
('/login' LoginUsers) -> To login the user
('/refresh', refresh) - to refresh the access token
('/logout', logout) -> to logout from the application
('/forgot-password', forgotpassword) -> The forgot password route
('/reset-password', resetPassword) -> The reset password route
('/google', googleAuthStart) -> The google oAuth route
('/google/callback', getAuthCallBackHandler) -> The google redirect handler route


